Question. Data type refers to the type of value of a variable has and the way the computer interprets it . Each data has a different size . You've studied 5 different data types and the size of data types. 
  Integer : 4 bytes , Long 8 bytes , float 4 bytes , double 8bytes , character 1 bytes , write a program in java , if data type given as input than size will come as output.


public class Solution {
    public static int dataTypes(String type) {
        
            switch(type){
                case "Integer":
                return 4;
                case "Long":
                return 8;
                case "Float":
                return 4;
                case "Double":
                return 8;
                case "Character":
                return 1;
                default:
                return -1;
            }
        


        
    }
}
    
